<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1888-03-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1888-03-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="271" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d271">
                    <head>No. 984.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Curry</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-03-21"><hi rend="italic">March</hi> 21,
                            1888</date>.</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 276.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your No. 304 of the 3d instant, inclosing copy
                        of the royal decree providing for an exposition at Madrid to celebrate the
                        four hundredth anniversary of the discovery of America, has been received
                        and a copy of it has been communicated to the Senate Committee on the
                        Centennial of the Constitution and the Discovery of America for their
                        information.</p>
                    <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                    <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">T. F. Bayard.</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>